Tamed Unit Dies
    Events
        Unit - A unit Takes damage
    Conditions
        Pet_Dead Equal to False
        (Damage Target) Equal to TamedUnit
        (Damage taken) Greater than or equal to ((Life of TamedUnit) - 0.41)
    Actions
        Custom script:   local string txt
        Custom script:   local player p
        -------- ===== --------
        Set VariableSet Pet_Dead = True
        -------- We don't really want the Tamed unit to die --------
        Event Response - Set Damage of Unit Damaged Event to ((Life of TamedUnit) - 1.00)
        Unit - Order TamedUnit to Stop.
        Unit - Make TamedUnit Invulnerable
        Unit - Change ownership of TamedUnit to Neutral Passive and Retain color
        Animation - Play TamedUnit's death animation
        Unit - Pause TamedUnit
        -------- Update multiboard --------
        Set VariableSet TamedUnitDeathCount = (TamedUnitDeathCount + 1)
        Multiboard - Set the text for Multiboard item in column 13, row 5 to (String(TamedUnitDeathCount))
        -------- Texts --------
        Custom script:   set txt = GetUnitName(udg_TamedUnit) + " is fatigued!"
        Custom script:    set p = GetOwningPlayer(udg_TamedUnit)
        -------- Start revival timer --------
        Set VariableSet Pet_DeathPoint = (Position of TamedUnit)
        Countdown Timer - Start ReviveTimerPet as a One-shot timer that will expire in 20.00 seconds
        -------- Duration = 2.0 sec, Size = 1.2, Color = reddish (100%, 5%, 10%) --------
        Custom script:   call FloatingTextTag.create(txt, udg_TamedUnit, 20.0, 1.2, p, 1.00, 0.05, 0.10, false, true)
        -------- Adjust animation --------
        Wait (Unit: TamedUnit's Real Field: Death Time (seconds) ('udtm')) seconds
        Animation - Change TamedUnit's animation speed to 0.00% of its original speed
